.TH man 5
.SH NAME
.PP
\*Lman\*O, \*Lman.page\*O \- The \*Lman\*O macro packages for reference pages
.SH SYNOPSIS
.PP
\*Ltbl \*Vfile\*O ... \*L| neqn | nroff \-h \*O[\*Voptions\*O] \*L\-man | \*O...
.nL
\*Ltbl \*Vfile\*O ... \*L| neqn | nroff \-h \*O[\*Voptions\*O]
\*L\-man.page | \*O...
.SH FLAGS
.PP
.VL 4m
.LI "\*L\-h\*O"
Uses output tabs during horizontal spacing to speed output and reduce
output character count.  Tab settings are assumed to be every eight
nominal character widths.
.LI "\*L-n\*VN\*O"
Numbers the first generated page as \*VN\*O.
.sp
Ignored by the \*Lman\*O macros for \*Lnroff\*O output.
Ignored for \*L*troff\*O output unless \*L-rp\*VS\*O is also specified.
.LI "\*L-rl\*VN\*O"
Turns on line double-spacing mode if \*VN\*O is greater than 0.
.LI "\*L-rn\*VN\*O"
Numbers the first generated page as \*VN\*O.
Page numbers always print on the outside end of the page footer.
.sp
Ignored by the \*Lman\*O macros for \*Lnroff\*O output.
.LI "\*L-rp\*VS\*O"
Sets the section number to \*VS\*O.  Section numbers appear in
output page footers as \*VS\*O\-\*VN\*O (chapter\-page-number).
.sp
Page numbers always print on the outside end of the page footer.
Starting page number defaults to ``1'' unless \*L-n\*VN\*O
or \*L-rn\*VN\*O is also specified.
.sp
Ignored by the \*Lman\*O macros for \*Lnroff\*O output.
.LI "\*L-rv2\*O"
Prints crop marks.  Only for use with \*L*troff\*O formatters.
.LE
.SH DESCRIPTION
.PP
.iX "-; man command" "man macro package"
.iX "-; troff text processor" "man macro package"
.iX "-; nroff text processor" "man macro package"
.iX "-[" "man macro package"
.iX "reference page" "formatting"
The \*Lman\*O macro package is used to format
reference pages for unpaginated viewing,
or for printing on ASCII printers.  The \*Lman\*O
macro package is the default.
The reference pages installed on the base system are formatted by the
\*Lman\*O and the \*Lcatman\*O
commands, using the \*Lman\*O macro package.
.PP
The \*Lman.page\*O macro package is used to format reference manual
pages for \*Epaginated\*O ASCII output.
.PP
The \*Vfile\*O argument is the name of the reference page source file.
.PP
The page width is 77 columns when formatted by the
\*Lnroff\*O(1) command and the \*Lman\*O or \*Lman.page\*O macro
packages.
The output is paginated when formatted by the \*Lnroff\*O command
and the \*Lman.page\*O macro package, with page numbers appearing
at the bottom right of each output page.
.SS Macros
.iX "-[" "man macro package" "macros"
The following describes the macros in the
\*Lman\*O and \*Lman.page\*O macro packages.
.PP
Note that some of the macro descriptions contain information
about \*L*troff\*O output.  This is provided for completeness,
only.  Digital does not supply or support
any \*L*troff\*O formatters.
.PP
Any
\*Vtext\*O
argument
can range from zero to six words.
Quotation marks (" ") can be used to include blanks in words.
If
\*Vtext\*O
is not specified,
special treatment is applied to
the next input line that has text to be printed.
In this way,
\*L\&.I\*O
can be used to italicize a whole line or
\*L\&.SM\*O
followed by
\*L\&.B\*O
to make small bold letters.
.PP
A prevailing indent distance is remembered between
successive indented paragraphs,
and is reset to a default value upon reaching a nonindented paragraph.
Default units for indents \*Vi\*O
are ens (an en is 1 \*Lnroff\*O
character or 1/2 em space in the current point size).
.PP
Typeface and size are reset to default values
before each paragraph, and after processing
font and size setting macros.
.PP
.IP "\&.AT [ \*L3\*O|\*L4\*O|\*L5\*O ] [ \*Vnumber\*O ]" 12
For \*L*troff\*O output only.  Specifies the text string to be
printed as the inside page footer.  No argument, or the argument \*L3\*O,
specifies the text "7th Edition."
The argument \*L4\*O specifies the text "System III."
The argument \*L5\*O specifies the text "System V."
The argument \*L5\*O followed by a \*Vnumber\*O argument
specifies the text "System V Release \*Vnumber\*O."
.IP "\&.B [ \*Vtext...\*O ]"
Sets text \*Vtext\*O in boldface.  If no text is specified,
only the next source text line is set in boldface.
.IP "\&.BI \*Vword1 word2\*O [ \*Vwords...\*O ]"
Sets \*Vword1\*O in boldface, \*Vword2\*O in an italic typeface, and then
alternates between these two fonts for the remaining words, up to six
words.  Blanks between words are stripped unless the string is enclosed
in quotation marks (" ").
.IP "\&.BR \*Vword1 word2\*O [ \*Vwords...\*O ]"
Sets \*Vword1\*O in boldface, \*Vword2\*O in a roman typeface, and
then alternates
between these two fonts for the remaining words, up to six words.
Blanks between words are stripped unless the string is enclosed
in quotation marks (" ").
.IP "\&.CM [ \*Vnumber\*O ]"
For \*L*troff\*O output only.  Specifies the text string to be
printed as the inside page footer.  No argument, or the number \*L1\*O,
specifies the text "1st Carnegie-Mellon Update."
The number \*L2\*O specifies the text "2nd Carnegie-Mellon Update."
The number \*L3\*O specifies the text "3rd Carnegie-Mellon Update."
Any whole number \*Vn\*O above \*L3\*O specifies the text
"\*Vn\*Oth Carnegie-Mellon Update."
.IP "\&.CT \*Vcharacter\*O"
