The example is set flush left unless an indent \*Vi\*O is specified.  Units
of \*Vi\*O are ens.
.IP "\&.G [ \*Vtext...\*O ]"
Sets \*Vtext\*O in a sans-serif typeface.  If no text is specified,
only the next source text line is set in a sans-serif typeface.
.IP "\&.GB [ \*Vwords...\*O ]"
Sets \*Vtext\*O in a sans-serif bold typeface.  If no text is specified,
only the next source text line is set in a sans-serif bold typeface.
.IP "\&.GL [ \*Vtext...\*O ]"
Sets \*Vtext\*O in a sans-serif italic typeface.  If no text is specified,
only the next source text line is set in a sans-serif italic typeface.
.IP "\&.HP [\|\*Vi\*O\|]\*O"
Begins a paragraph with a hanging indent of \*Vi\*O ens.
.IP "\&.I [ \*Vtext...\*O ]"
Sets \*Vtext\*O in an italic typeface.  If no text is specified,
only the next source text line is set in an italic typeface.
.IP "\&.I1 \*Vword\*O"
Sets a temporary indent to the length of the specified word.
.IP "\&.I2 \*Vword\*O"
Reverses one line and then sets a temporary indent to the length of
