.IP "\&.IB \*Vword1 word2\*O [ \*Vwords...\*O ]"
Sets \*Vword1\*O in an italic typeface, \*Vword2\*O in boldface, and then
alternates between these two fonts for the remaining words, up to six
words.  Blanks between words are stripped unless the string is enclosed
in quotation marks (" ").
.IP "\&.IP \*Vx \*O[\|i\*O\|]\*O"
Sets the prevailing indent to \*Vi\*O.  Then begins the indented
paragraph with a hanging tag given by the next text line.  If the tag
does not fit, the macro places the next text on a separate line.
Tag \*Vx\*O appears in bold typeface.
.IP "\&.IR \*Vword1 word2\*O [ \*Vwords...\*O ]"
Sets \*Vword1\*O in an italic typeface, \*Vword2\*O in a roman typeface,
