.IP "\&.PN \*Vx\*O [ \*Vy\*O ]"
Sets \*Vx\*O in an italic or constant width typeface (depending on
the
\*L*roff\*O
formatter type) and then reverts to the previous typeface.
The optional argument \*Vy\*O is appended to \*Vx\*O with
no space, but printed in the previous typeface.
The \*Vx\*O argument is usually a path name;
\*Vy\*O is usually punctuation.
.IP "\&.Pn \*Vx y\*O [ \*Vz\*O ]"
Sets \*Vx\*O in the current typeface, sets \*Vy\*O in an italic or constant
width typeface (depending on the
\*L*roff\*O
formatter type) and appends it to \*Vx\*O, and finally
reverts to the previous typeface.
The optional argument \*Vz\*O is appended to \*Vy\*O, but printed in the
previous typeface.  Spaces are removed between \*Vx\*O, \*Vy\*O, and \*Vz\*O,
unless quotation marks (" ") are used to enclose strings with spaces.
The \*Vx\*O argument is usually a fixed path name; \*Vy\*O is
usually a variable path name; and \*Vz\*O is usually punctuation.
