.SS Defaults
Automatic hyphenation is turned on. However, \*Vlast\*O lines (ones that will
cause a trap) are not hyphenated and the last and first two characters of
a word are not split off.
.PP
Characters printed from the Special Font are artificially bolded by three units
whenever the current font is `3'.
.PP
The default page width is 77 columns for
\*Lnroff\*O output and 8.5 inches for output generated by
\*L*troff\*O text formatters.
For \*Lnroff\*O output, section headers and page headers
are output flush left, primary paragraphs are indented two columns,
and the maximum line length is a total of 77 columns for an effective
right margin of \&.3 inches.  This allows for printing on A4 paper.
Left and right page margins are 7.5 picas when
\*L*troff\*O text formatters are used.
.PP
The default page length is unlimited (unpaginated) for
\*Lnroff\*O output with the \*Lman\*O macros, and is 66 lines long for
\*Lnroff\*O with the \*Lman.page\*O macros.
The default page length is 11 inches for output generated by
\*L*troff\*O text formatters.
.PP
The \*L\&.TH\*O macro sets up the following defaults:
.IP \(bu 4
Text is set in ``noadjust'' mode; the right margin is ragged.
.IP \(bu 4
The default interparagraph distance is 1v for
\*Lnroff\*O and \&.5v for \*L*troff\*O text formatters.
.IP \(bu 4
The basic text indent is two columns for
\*Lnroff\*O
and four picas for
\*L*troff\*O
text formatters, from the left margin.
.IP \(bu 4
The maximum text line length is 7.5 inches for \*Lnroff\*O
and 36 picas for \*L*troff\*O text formatters.
.IP \(bu 4
Sets tab stops every 8 ens for \*Lnroff\*O and every \&.5 inches
for \*L*troff\*O text formatters.
.IP \(bu 4
The basic text point size is 11 points, with line spacing set to 12 points.
.IP \(bu 4
The basic text font is ``R'' (a roman typeface).
.IP \(bu 4
Reference page headers, section headers, and subsection headers are set
in a sans-serif bold typeface for \*L*troff\*O formatters.
.PP
There are no page footers for \*Lnroff\*O output with the \*Lman\*O
macros.  Page footers are printed when using \*L*troff\*O formatters,
and when using the \*Lman.page\*O macros with either \*Lnroff\*O
or \*L*troff\*O.
.PP
The default page number, when footers are printed, has the format:
.oS
name(c[s])-pg
.oE
where:
.VL 5m
.LI "name"
is the \*L\&.TH\*O \*Vn\*O argument
.LI "c[s]"
is the \*L\&.TH \*Vc\*O[\*Vs\*O] argument (section[subsection])
.LI "pg"
is the current page number
.LE
.PP
By default, the page number prints on the right side of the page foot.
.PP
When printing multiple pages, the page number is reset to ``1''
at the start of each new reference page.
