Sections 5, 6, and the single-letter sections listed in the \*Lman\*O(1)
reference page normally do not have subsections, so none should be
specified.
.PP
Subsections ``.z'' and ``.Z'' are not valid and should never be used.
.PP
For \*Lnroff\*O output, keep the size of the reference page name, including
its section and subsection, to a maximum of 38 characters to prevent
overprinting in the reference page header.  Similarly, restrict the
size of the \*Vo\*O and \*Va\*O fields to a maximum of 38 characters.
If the \*Vhc\*O
field is used, reduce the size of the name, section, and
subsection fields by the size of the \*Vhc\*O field + 1.
.PP
The maximum sizes for the reference page name, \*Vo\*O and \*Va\*O
fields, are much shorter if the reference page is formatted with a
\*L*troff\*O formatter.
