.SS The NAME Section
.if n .PP
The
\*Lcatman\*O
command assumes the NAME section of a reference page has the
following format:
.oS
name[, name, name ...] - explanatory text
.oE
There should be at least one space after any comma and only one space
following the ``hyphen'' (-).  A ``backslash hyphen'' (\e-) may
also be used to produce a longer dash.
.\"Avoid using \*L*roff\*O commands in the NAME section.
Avoid using macros or other markup to code information in the NAME section.
The explanatory text should be brief.
The \*Lcatman\*O
command combines information in the NAME section with parameters of the
\*L\&.TH\*O macro to create an entry in a database searched by the
\*Lapropos\*O(1), \*Lman\*O(1), and \*Lwhatis\*O(1) commands.
.SH PORTABILITY CONSIDERATIONS
.PP
The DEC OSF/1 \*Lman\*O
macro packages contain extensions and enhancements borrowed from
other macro packages.  If you need to write portable reference pages,
you should not use the following macros:
.RS
.PP
.TS
tab(@);
l l l l l l.
AT@CM@CT@CW@De@Ds
EE@EX@G@GB@GL@I1
I2@LP@MS@NE@NT@PN
Pn@R@RN@UC@UF
.TE
.PP
.RE
The \*L\&.LP\*O macro is obsolete,
but is provided for backward compatibility with other vendors.
.PP
The \*L\&.TH\*O
macro permits the use of the percent (%) character in any
of its fields.  The presence of the percent character may cause
problems for other implementations of this macro.
.PP
The width of the \*Lnroff\*O output is 77 columns, with a 2-column
indent, for an effective maximum line length of 75 columns.
On other systems, the width of the \*Lnroff\*O output may be only
65 columns, with a 5-column indent, for an effective maximum line
length of 60 columns.  Avoid creating tables and no-fill text
that require the full 75 columns available on DEC OSF/1.  Plan for
a maximum line length of 60 columns, instead.
.\".PP
